    • Method Detail

      • onServiceUpdate

        void onServiceUpdate(ServiceState state)
        Notifies about a new position estimate from the IndoorAtlas service. The position of the device is available in alternative coordinate systems through the state parameter. The heading of the device is available in both radians and degrees. Calls on onServiceUpdate start occurring periodically immediately after startPositioning in interface IndoorAtlas has been successfully completed, indicated through a notify call on onServiceInitialized. For more information, see ServiceState.
        Parameters:
        state - the new position of the device

      • onServiceFailure

        void onServiceFailure(int errorCode,
                      java.lang.String reason)
        Notifies about a failure related to communication with IndoorAtlas.
        Parameters:
        errorCode - error code
        reason - a human readable description of the cause of the failure

      • onServiceStopped

        Notifies that the positioning session has been torn down.

      • onCalibrationReady

        void onCalibrationReady()
        Notifies that calibration has reached level of quality that provides best possible positioning accuracy. This callback may be invoked several time during positioning session, whenever high quality threshold has been reached.

      • onCalibrationInvalid

        @Deprecated
void onCalibrationInvalid()
        Deprecated. As of version 1.4, this callback is not invoked anymore.
        Notifies that calibration is too old or otherwise invalid.

      • onCalibrationFailed

        @Deprecated
void onCalibrationFailed(java.lang.String reason)
        Deprecated. As of version 1.4, this callback is not invoked anymore.
        Notifies about a failure in calibrating the device.
        Parameters:
        reason - a human readable description of the cause of the failure

      • onCalibrationStatus

        void onCalibrationStatus(CalibrationState calibrationState)
        Notifies about current calibration status. You can expect these throughout the SDK’s lifecycle when performing initial calibration or when it has significant changes. The frequency will drop once high calibration has been reached.

      • onNetworkChangeComplete

        void onNetworkChangeComplete(boolean success)
        Notifies about network preference result.
        Parameters:
        success - true if the operation succeeded. In the case the hipri tear down does not succeed, failure is reported after a few retries.
